  <T n="category">488441<!--TutorialCategory: tutorial_Category_EP21_ProjectGold--></T>
  <T n="name">0xBB12B54A<!--String: "Welcome to Ondarion"--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP21\UI\Tutorial\EP21_Lessons_Ondarion.png">2f7d0004:00000000:8f9be6f3890a73a4</T>
      <T n="text">0x73B38EDF<!--String: "Welcome to Ondarion, a <b><font color='#199C2C'>Kingdom</font></b> of Nobles and great Dynasties. This is a place where opulence and ancient traditions reign supreme.\n\nOne such tradition is <b><font color='#199C2C'>Swordsmanship</font></b>. There's no better place to train, and prove your skill than at the open dueling areas in each of Ondarion's neighborhoods.\nAnother great tradition is the <b><font color='#199C2C'>Waltz</font></b>. In each neighborhood you'll find romantic corners with public Dance Floors for Waltzing, where you may practice alone or with a partner.\n\nDo watch out for Ondarion's <b><font color='#199C2C'>Royal Robber</font></b>...they're a local figure known for stealing from the rich, but occasionally giving to those who are running out of Simoleons.\n\nThere's many other mysteries and locations rooted in old legends to be found in Ondarion, so always keep an eye out!"--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP21\UI\Tutorial\EP21_Lessons_Ondarion2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:105d13d1dcc27f9e</T>
      <T n="text">0x39A0D8F2<!--String: "<b><font color='#199C2C'>Dambele</font></b> is a warm and welcoming neighborhood, with a focus on fostering community and promoting the arts.\n\nThere's no better place to experience its warmth than at the local <b><font color='#199C2C'>Community Market</font></b>! This is a new Lot Type where Sims will gather to sell their crafts, play music, recite books, cook for one another, or simply hang out together and with their children.\n\nAnother new Lot Type you can visit in Dambele is the <b><font color='#199C2C'>Backroom</font></b>. A Backroom is a venue that can be set up to function during daytime as a <b><font color='#199C2C'>Library, a Museum or a Gym</font></b>. However, it also hides a <b><font color='#199C2C'>Nightclub</font></b> inside, where Sims will go dancing at night."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP21\UI\Tutorial\EP21_Lessons_Ondarion3.png">2f7d0004:00000000:105d13d1dcc27f9f</T>
      <T n="text">0x87323EFB<!--String: "<b><font color='#199C2C'>Bellacorde</font></b> is a neighborhood rooted in old traditions of chivalry, elegance and...pretentiousness.\n\n<b><font color='#199C2C'>La Vivace</font></b> is the local lounge, a historic location where generations of Nobles have Waltzed to prove themselves among high society. This is the perfect spot to host a fancy <b><font color='#199C2C'>Grand Ball event</font></b>.\n\nThe <b><font color='#199C2C'>Apartment</font></b> building of Bellacorde is built by the central square. It's a great option for those who prefer not having to build their own house (and can afford the overpriced costs of this neighborhood).\n\nBy the central square you will also find a unique Trade Stall. It offers a <b><font color='#199C2C'>daily selection of odds and ends</font></b> that are uncommon to find outside Ondarion."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP21\UI\Tutorial\EP21_Lessons_Ondarion4.png">2f7d0004:00000000:105d13d1dcc27f98</T>
      <T n="text">0xB861D8B7<!--String: "<b><font color='#199C2C'>Verdemar</font></b> is a neighborhood with a colorful history, where pirates and Nobles have coexisted and entwined for generations. Indeed, this is the place Princess Cordelia called home for many years.\n\nIt's still common for the shadier people of Ondarion to hang out at the <b><font color='#199C2C'>local Bar</font></b>. This is where you're more likely to meet blackmailers, <b><font color='#199C2C'>Information Brokers</font></b>, or maybe even the infamous <b><font color='#199C2C'>Royal Robber</font></b>.\n\nVerdemar is also a wonderful place for the adventurous, and those who love <b><font color='#199C2C'>sailing</font></b>—you can grab a boat, and explore the emerald waters of Ondarion! You may even find some old <b><font color='#199C2C'>treasure chests</font></b> popping up from time to time on the shores."--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
